1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with statistical characterization of a new fading distribution and its application in analyzing performance metrics like outage probability and channel capacity. This falls under the purview of information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the performance analysis of wireless communication systems over the proposed fading distribution. This is relevant to the networking and internet architecture community. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper does not explicitly deal with social networks, but the proposed fading distribution can be used to model wireless communication in social networks. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): Similar to cs.COMM, the paper's focus on wireless communication systems makes it relevant to the networking and internet architecture community. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper does not deal with multiagent systems, but the proposed fading distribution can be used to model wireless communication in multiagent systems.
